Add support for use within AWS GovCloud

GovCloud does not have multiple zones (ATM) so I had to prevent the
_get_region method from stripping off the last character in the zone. I
got errors when setting the placement so I assume this parameter needs
to be ignored when in GovCloud. Last, boto needed to be upgraded in
order to support the new GovCloud region.

Removing the @ symbol.  Was getting confused with curl.  Oops.

Fixes support for posting contents of a file

In order for the contents of a file to be posted with ab you must proceed the file path with an @ symbol.

Adds support for passing the pem key when scp'ing the data file to the bee instance

The scp was failing because it doesn't specify the .pem key in the command.  This includes it in the command.

Merge pull request #61 from Altonymous/patch-1

Fixes VPC support when there are name collisions between the security groups

Cleaning up formatting.

It looks like whoever added the _get_security_group_ids(...) method  used tabs while the rest of the project uses spaces.  I have converted the function to spaces.

Also cleaned up the placement of subnet_id since it was indented with tabs as well.

Fixes VPC support when there are name collisions between the security groups

This checks if subnet is set and if so it only looks for a match on the name when the vpc_id is not None.  Otherwise, if subnet is None then it makes sure the vpc_id is also None
